President Cyril Ramaphosa is hosting Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni at the Union Buildings.  JOHANNESBURG - Political and trade relations will feature as President Cyril Ramaphosa hosts Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni. The East African leader is in the country on his first state visit since 2011. Continental peace and security will also be on the agenda, with both countries playing a role in conflict resolution. The pair are also set to participate in a business forum a little later.